Among the controversial EU regulations are the mandatory incorporation of bioethanol into fuels that are subsequently harmful to the natural environment, the prohibition of reliable mercury thermometers, because they contain a relatively small amount of this dangerous substance, or the directive on the size of chicken cages, because eggs have become much more expensive this year.
Criticism in the past also reaped the actual ban on the use of the term "butter spread" or the ban on the sale of conventional light bulbs.
Bananas must be 14 cm long
